description:
US HARD ROCK MAPLE 
With coloured top sheets and sidewalls

THE WOOD - "Sugar Maple"

So called Sugar Maple because of it's sweet sap. It is the main species used today for maple syrup production along with Black maple, though Sugar Maple is preferred and it's sap has twice the sugar content of other Maple species. The trees can grow to a height of 40 meters and live for up to 500 years old. It's wood is sort after for it's hard, heavy, strong and high impact resistant properties.

The prints are hand screen printed onto plastic backing sheets, yours are printed in full colour CMYK process printing, then they are heat transferred onto the decks.
